EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO HIGHWAYS -- RELOCATION OF UTILITY SERVICES
***
1 This act would provide that the cost of relocation of utility facilities necessitated by
2 highway construction shall be reimbursed by the state at fifty percent (50%) of the reasonable
3 amount to private corporations and companies. The cost of relocation shall be fully reimbursed by
4 the state for relocation of utility facilities owned by municipalities and political subdivisions.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
